      • execute

        public java.lang.String execute(java.lang.String request)
        Description copied from class: BasicAppInterfaceConnection

        String-oriented variant of the BasicAppInterfaceConnection.execute(Request) method. Accepts requests and returns responses encoded in the XML runtime data syntax specified in the chapter "XML Interfaces of the Application Interface Server" of the "Application Interface Programming Reference Manual."

        If the connection has not explicitly been opened with BasicAppInterfaceConnection.open(), then it will automatically be opened, the request executed in a separate session, and finally the connection closed. Alternatively, the connection may first be opened explicitly, after which all subsequent invocations of execute() will be processed in the same session until the connection is explicitly closed with BasicAppInterfaceConnection.close(). In this regard, see also AppInterfaceCommand.execute().

        Specified by:
        execute in interface AppInterfaceConnection
        Specified by:
